+## Routing boundary summary
+
+| Finding outcome | Route |
+|---|---|
+| `P0` or applicable `P1` hold / escalation | escalation surface; Hygiene records and routes, but does not own stop law |
+| promotion integrity issue | promotion path; Hygiene records the issue, but does not approve truth mutation |
+| non-blocking hygiene backlog | night-planning or backlog surface; Hygiene recommends sequencing, but does not become planning law |
+| state recommendation | bounded recommendation only; Hygiene does not directly mutate operational state |
+| ordinary cleanup | hygiene backlog or bounded cleanup batch with evidence-backed closure |
+
+## Cross-agent ownership check
+
+Before routing or closing a finding, classify whether ownership belongs to Hygiene, Routing, Informatics, Meta Detective, Promotion, Escalation, or another bounded owner. Hygiene records the classification and evidence, but does not absorb another agent's authority by auditing it.
 
